(d) Later daily windspeed build-up and duration of wind. 
(e) More homogeneous soil profile: Hames Valley with 
one principal soil type; Salinas Valley, over 70 soil types. 
(f) Geographically distinct and separate from the 
Salinas River Valley. 


Viticultural Area Boundary 


The boundary of the Hames Valley viticultural area may 
be found on one United States Geological Survey map, 
entitled Bradley Quadrangle, 15 minute series, with a scale 
of 1:62,500. The boundary is described in  9.147. 


