Federal Register

 notice that trustee officials may recover only those costs that are associated with the actual assessment. 


Response:

 As noted in the August 1, 1986, and the July 22, 1993, 

Federal Register

 notices, the Department believes that trustee officials will generally need the assistance of an interdisciplinary
team of experts when performing natural resource damage assessments. The rule does not restrict recoverable assessment
