official for, and specifically allocable to, site specific efforts taken in the assessment of damages.'' Therefore,
if attorneys are involved in work specifically allocable to an assessment, the resulting attorneys' fees are recoverable
as assessment costs under the rule. The rule does not address the recovery of attorneys' fees incurred in litigation
over the results of the damage assessment, as opposed to those incurred during the assessment itself. 


